UID:event_314183050@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260411T025615Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260410T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260410T230000
SUMMARY:Friday Casual Board Game Night
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Heavy Boardgamers\nFriday Casual Board Game Night is b
 ack at Wild Wing on King Street West!\n\nJoin us for an evening of light t
 o medium board games\, good conversation\, and meeting new people after a 
 long week. Players of all levels are welcome\, whether you’re a regular 
 gamer or just curious to try something new.\n\nWe’ll kick things off at 
 6:00 p.m. with a few easy party games to help everyone settle in and mingl
 e\, then split off into smaller groups as the night goes on. Coming solo i
 s totally fine. This is a casual\, newcomer-friendly meetup.\n\nSince the 
 venue is still building its board game collection\, feel free to bring you
 r own games if you’d like\, and let us know in the comments! I’ll also
  be bringing a few party games for others to borrow.\n\nVenue Minimum Spen
 d:\nWild Wing has a $15 minimum spend per person. If you order food or dri
 nks\, that amount goes toward the minimum. If you don’t order anything\,
  the $15 will simply count as your admission.\n\nLooking forward to seeing
  everyone there!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/toronto-heavy-boardgamers/events/3141
 83050/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260408T172011Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260408T172011Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Toronto Heavy Boardgamers
UID:event_313896491@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260411T025615Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T180000
SUMMARY:Toronto Mid-Town Weekend Gaming @ The Guild House
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Heavy Boardgamers\nWelcome to the Saturday meetup for 
 Toronto Heavy Boardgamers @ The Guild House!\n\nThe purpose of this event 
 is to meet up to play heavier / longer board games\, and have fun while do
 ing it! We will start off small and if there is sufficient interest we wil
 l add capacity for future events.\n\nYou are welcome to bring your own gam
 es to the event\, or use the games in the library at the location.\n\n**Sc
 heduling details:**\n\\- If you have a specific game that you would like t
 o post for\\\, feel free to do so in comments\\. In your post\\\, include 
 the name of the game\\\, number of players needed for the game\\\, whether
  you are offering a teach or not\\\, and the start time \\(please try to s
 tart before noon if possible\\)\\.\n\\- If you would like to join a specif
 ic game that has already been posted\\\, feel free to comment on it confir
 ming your participation\\. Make sure you have noted the details posted by 
 the host\\.\n\\- You are of course also welcome to organize / join games o
 nsite on the day itself\\\, assuming sufficient players / tables are avail
 able\n\n**Rules around COVID:**\n\\- Given this is a public event\\\, we r
 espectfully ask that only i\\) fully vaccinated individuals\\\, and ii\\) 
 those not exhibiting any COVID symptoms\\\, participate\\. This requiremen
 t may change in the future based on provincial guidelines and group requir
 ements\n\n**Available Amenities:**\n\\- Food and drinks are available on\\
 -site\\\, you can see a detailed menu [here](https://theguildhouse.ca/page
 s/menu). **Outside food and drinks are not allowed by the Guild House.**\n
 \\- There is an on\\-site game library\\\, and use of it is covered within
  the admission fee\\.\n\n**Admission Fee:**\n\\- There is a $10 fee charge
 d by the establishment for use of space\\. Payments are to be made directl
 y to the establishment at the time of entry and not to the organizer
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/toronto-heavy-boardgamers/events/3138
 96491/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260322T155626Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260322T155626Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
